====================================================================================================
FERMION MASS PRIMES TEST 19
Held-out cycle closure
====================================================================================================
Graph-closure test on the modal-equivalence reading. Tree built from
two cross-family bridges (t/tau, t/b) plus within-family edges.
Predicts seven held-out cross-family edges; tests whether predictions
match observation across nine common scales.

Reading rules (per cell, |compositional residual|):
  Strong:  <= 5%
  Modest:  5  < x <= 15%
  Weak:    15 < x <= 30%
  None:    > 30%

Identity check tolerance: 1e-09
Direct fit small threshold: 3.0%
Grammar floor: R = 3.0

Held-out edges:
  c/s      = t/b x b/s / t/c
  d/u      = t/c x c/u / t/b / b/s / s/d
  u/e      = t/tau x tau/mu x mu/e / t/c / c/u
  c/mu     = t/tau x tau/mu / t/c
  d/e      = t/tau x tau/mu x mu/e / t/b / b/s / s/d
  mu/s     = t/b x b/s / t/tau / tau/mu
  b/tau    = t/tau / t/b

Scales: 9 common scales (PDG excluded by design)
Candidates generated: 346 (2^a x p up to 1015)

